What is so called big data?

  • Wikipedia says : Big data usually includes data sets with sizes beyond the ability of commonly used software tools to capture, curate, manage, and process the data within a tolerable elapsed time.
  • 3V, some people add another V for value, some add even more

    source: http://kavyamuthanna.files.wordpress.com/2013/01/picture-11.png
  • Its a concept, not actual size
  • Most of you who will work as a data scientist may not even see big data

What is data science?

Taken from your comments on homework zero

  • Data science is used in the analysis of data. Data analysis is important for making companies more efficient by finding patterns in the data that company compiles.
  • Data Science is a new technology that works with big data
  • Data Science is a collaboration of several fields of study in an effort to form a new strategic and intelligent way of describing and presenting a very large data set.
  • Data science is being able to extract useful knowledge from any data set
  • It is used to organize large amounts of data created in most companies
  • I understand data science to be the study of identifying relationships/patterns
  • I do not know much about Data Science but I am interested

Definition: Data Science

  • Arts and Science of transforming data
  • Data products

Data Science is not computer science

  • Data management
  • Data technology
  • Data access
  • Reports

Data Science is not statistics

  • Well, Cleveland's article says some of it, I leave it a homework problem
  • Does Statistics focus on data product?
  • Lots of data are now generated without having any statistical planning, but they can still provide deliverable data products

What is data product?

Data product

  • A data dependent product that has some commercial value
    • Could be another data set summarizing the original bigger data set
    • An online tool to visualize or explore important information
    • Mobile app
    • Could be a report based on data




  • Can a journal article be a data product?
